<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[191,1440,1458,1552]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,346,1458,1484]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Monzon, Blackaller, and Hawks" authorityYear="2020" box="[352,560,1458,1484]" class="Insecta" family="Rutelidae" genus="Chrysina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clavellina">
<emphasis box="[352,560,1458,1484]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Chrysina clavellina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
currently is known only from two specimens collected at high elevations (2,647 and 2,745 meters above sea level) in the pine-oak habitat of La Cumbre, Santiago Clavellinas and Santa Inés del Monte in the Sierra Azul in 
<collectingRegion box="[504,589,1526,1552]" country="Mexico" name="Oaxaca" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Oaxaca</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[600,685,1526,1552]" name="Mexico" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Mexico</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
